value.value: Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + lysine in peptide = CoA + N-acetyl-lysine-peptide.

The selective autophagy process in which a mitochondrion is degraded by macroautophagy in a process initiated by mitochondrial depolarization (mtDepo) followed by Parkin binding, and ubiquitination of outer membrane proteins, to remove potentially harm-inducing dysfunctional/damaged mitochondria.
The membrane invagination process by which an autophagosomal membrane surrounds an object that will be degraded by macroautophagy.
A G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by leukotriene binding to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process.
The autophagy process by which cytosolic proteins targeted for degradation are tagged with a chaperone and are directly transferred into and degraded in a late endosomal compartment.

label.value: protein lipidation involved in autophagosome assembly

value.value: The protein lipidation process by which phosphatidylethanolamine is conjugated to a protein of the ATG8 family, leading to membrane insertion of the protein as a step in autophagosome assembly.

label.value: protein targeting to lysosome involved in chaperone-mediated autophagy

value.value: The targeting of a protein to the lysosome process in which an input protein binds to a chaperone and subsequently to a lysosomal receptor.
A lysosomal membrane protein complex that enables the translocation of a target protein across the lysosomal membrane as part of chaperone-mediated autophagy.
Any process in which an organism acquires a novel neuromuscular action or movement as the result of experience.
The specific neuromuscular movement of a single organism in response to external or internal stimuli.
Unwinding a DNA helix containing forked DNA, driven by ATP hydrolysis.
Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + sphingomyelin = ceramide + choline phosphate + H+ in an acidic environment.
Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + sphingomyelin = ceramide + choline phosphate + H+ in a neutral environment.

Binding to long non-coding RNA molecules transcribed from subtelomeric regions in most eukaryotes. Telomeric repeat-containing RNA (TERRA) molecules consist of subtelomeric-derived sequences and G-rich telomeric repeats.
The localization process by which an autophagic substrate is delivered to a forming autophagosome.

label.value: negative regulation of circulating fibrinogen levels

value.value: Any process that reduces the quantity of fibrinogen circulating in the bloodstream.

label.value: positive regulation of circulating fibrinogen levels

value.value: Any process that increases the quantity of fibrinogen circulating in the bloodstream.

label.value: leukocyte adhesion to vascular endothelial cell

value.value: The attachment of a leukocyte to vascular endothelial cell via adhesion molecules.

label.value: leukocyte adhesion to arterial endothelial cell

value.value: The attachment of a leukocyte to an arterial endothelial cell via adhesion molecules.
Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-2-hydroxyglutarate + acceptor -> 2-oxoglutarate + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoglutarate + reduced acceptor -> (S)-2-hydroxyglutarate + acceptor.

An defense response against a fungus mediated through an innate immune response. An innate immune response is mediated by germline encoded components that directly recognize components of potential pathogens.
Binding to an alpha-latrotoxin receptor.

The series of molecular signals in which calmodulin-dependent protein kinase activity enabled by a CAMKK directly activates an AMPK. The cascade begins with calmodulin binding calcium which in turn binds CAMKK enabling its calmodulin-dependent protein kinase activity. The cascade ends with AMP-activated protein kinase activity.
The organelle membrane fusion process in which the membrane of a multivesicular body fuses with a lysosome to create a hybrid organelle.

label.value: late endosome to lysosome transport via multivesicular body sorting pathway

value.value: The directed movement of substances from late endosomes to lysosomes by a pathway in which molecules are sorted into multivesicular bodies, which then fuse with the lysosome.

label.value: positive regulation of lung blood pressure

value.value: The process that increases the force with which blood travels through the lungs.

label.value: negative regulation of lung blood pressure

value.value: The process that decreases the force with which blood travels through the lungs.
Catalysis of the reaction: Na+(in) + Mg2+(out) = Na+(out) + Mg2+(in).
Catalysis of the reaction: N-ribosylnicotinate + ATP = ADP + 2 H+ + nicotinate mononucleotide.
Binding to a translation elongation factor, any polypeptide factor involved in the peptide elongation in ribosome-mediated translation.

A change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a caloric restriction, insufficient food energy intake.
The directed movement of a xenobiotic through the blood-nerve barrier.
A chromatin silencing complex that recruits histone-modifying enzymes and upregulates silencing of rDNA in response to glucose starvation.
Negative regulation of sister chromatid cohesion by the topological unlinking of a cohesin ring to DNA.
Facilitating a conformational change to load a cohesin complex around sister chromatids.
A DNA binding activity in which a protein complex interacts with at least one DNA duplex to encircle the DNA molecules with a loose fitting ring.

Subunit of the MHC class I peptide loading complex (GO:0042824) (=PLC) involved in the assembly of the heavy-chain-beta2-microglobulin dimers of the MHC class I molecules that fold with eight to ten residue peptides in the endoplasmic reticulum. Required for the inhibition of the reduction of the disulfide bonds of the heavy chains and the assembly and stabilization of the PLC, suggesting it may play a structural rather than a catalytic role.
The protein localization to chromatin by which a cohesin ring complex is topologically linked to DNA as part of the mitotic cell cycle.
Negative regulation of sister chromatid cohesion by the topological unlinking of a cohesin ring to DNA as part of the mitotic cell cycle.
Fusion of the membrane of a transport vesicle with a target membrane on another vesicle.
A catalytic activity that contributes to the degradation of peptidoglycan.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1->4)-beta linkages of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine (GlcNAc) from peptidoglycan.
An endopeptidase activity that uses peptidoglycan as a substrate.
A peptidoglycan endopeptidase activity that acts on a stem peptide of peptidoglycan.
A peptidoglycan endopeptidase activity that acts on a peptidoglycan cross-bridge.
Binding to Epidermal Growth Factor (EGF) repeats.

A process that converts unprimed dense core granules (DCVs) to a pool of primed vesicles that are capable of fusing with the plasma membrane (fusion-competent) and thereby releasing their contents. Priming typically occurs after docking.
The initial attachment of a dense core granule membrane to the plasma membrane.
A motor activity driven by GTP hydrolysis.
